It's not a job. It's not a profession. It's our way of life.
At Patterson-UTI Drilling Company, working incident free is our way of life. When you're part of our team, you're part of our family. Your safety and wellbeing matter to us. So, working incident free isn't just a priority to us. It’s our way of life.
Operational excellence is our minimum standard. We don't settle for mediocrity. Whether you work on one of our rigs, on one of our trucks or in one of our yards, through you, our operational processes deliver. Excellence is our way of life.
Development of our people is a core value at Patterson-UTI Drilling Company. Whether you are new to our industry or just new to our company, our Competency Development and Learning Programs give you the tools for success right from the start. Continuous learning is our way of life.
We are committed to growing our own.  We coach, we counsel and we mentor. Growing our own is our way of life.
Opportunities to join our way of life include all rig-based positions, and from time to time, operations management, rig move trucking, maintenance, HSE, and HR.
Patterson-UTI Drilling Company proudly supports our troops and values their talents and contributions. We actively recruit military service members and qualified veterans.
If you're interested in our way of life, please access our Careers Site link at the top of the page to create your candidate profile and review available vacancies.
Please note:

Patterson-UTI Drilling Company only accepts applications online through our Company's website. We do not accept paper applications in any form including fax, email or in person. We will not retain unsolicited applications submitted outside our online process.
If you are interested in opportunities to join our Company, please create your candidate profile on one of our Careers sites above. Those sites provide instructions on how to create your candidate profile and apply to open vacancies and, give answers to frequently asked questions and technical support. For candidates without internet access, computer stations are available in our local hiring offices during regular business hours. To find a hiring office, visit our Contact Us page.
Patterson-UTI Drilling Company is an equal opportunity employer that prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type and affords equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants, without regard to age, race, sex, color, religion, national origin, disability, marital status, covered veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity, or any other characteristic protected under state or local law.
We are committed to a drug-free workplace. Applicants receiving conditional job offers will be required to successfully pass a pre-employment drug test. Refusal to take a drug test or a positive test will result in loss of conditional job offer.
Applicants are required to submit accurate, complete and truthful information when answering questions during the Company's online application, interview and hiring process. Failure to do so, including providing partial or inaccurate information, will be grounds for rejection of a candidate's application(s) or separation from the Company if the individual has begun employment.
The Company conducts background checks on all applicants receiving conditional job offers.  You will be required to sign an authorization form so the Company may run the background check.  Our receipt of adverse information does not necessarily disqualify you from employment.  We evaluate the circumstances on a case-by-case basis in accordance with the law.
No question in the application process will be used to limit or excuse an applicant's consideration for employment on a basis prohibited by local, state or federal law. It is the Company's policy not to refuse to hire a qualified individual with a disability because of the individual's need for an accommodation that would be required by local, state or federal law.
If you have a disability that requires an accommodation to assist you with our online application process, please email recruiting@patenergy.com and provide us with the job number or job title, location of the position(s) of interest and your name, telephone number, email address and best time of day for us to reach you. Please allow three (3) business days for a response. Please note: This option applies only to those individuals with disabilities who require assistance with the Company's online application process. Resumes and applications for employment will not be accepted through this address and will be disregarded.   








